By Omolola Afolabi  St. Nicholas, one of the largest private hospitals in Lagos has announced the suspension of activities in its Lagos Island branch. In a press statement signed by its clinical director, Dr.Ebun Bamgboye, the hospital disclosed that its decision was as a result of exposure to COVID-19. The hospital also said it has contacted the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) while its facility has been decontaminated by the Lagos state government. “The safety of all our staff and patients is of paramount importance to us. As such, we are complying with the directive of the HEFAMAA (Health Facility Monitoring and Accreditation Agency) to suspend our services for 2 weeks (Saturday 18th April 2020 — Saturday 2′ May 2020),” the hospital said. “We understand the critical needs of our patients, hence we have introduced our telemedicine services where patients can consult our doctors via video and audio channels by calling.” The hospital, however, pointed out that its Victoria Island branch will remain open. 